by KSI featuring Jme |url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/53669513/credits |website=Tidal |accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n| producer   = * [[Sway (musician)|Sway]]\n* [[Show N Prove]]<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| chronology = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| prev_title = [[Lamborghini (song)|Lamborghini]]\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title = Goes Off\n| next_year  = 2016\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Jme (musician)|Jme]]\n | type       = Singles\n | prev_title = Man Don't Care\n | prev_year  = 2015\n | title      = Keep Up\n | year       = 2015\n | next_title = House & Pop\n | next_year  = 2016\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|uBosAirL8ds|\"Keep Up\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Keep Up'''\" is a song by English YouTube personality and rapper [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]], featuring English MC [[Jme (musician)|Jme]]. It was released on 13 November 2015 and is KSI's first single to be released through [[Island Records]] after recently signing to the record label. It is the lead single from KSI's 2016 debut [[Keep Up (EP)|extended play of the same name]]. The song charted at number 45 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20151120/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref> The song was originally scheduled for release on 1 January 2016, but was brought forward due to the song's appearance on the compilation album [[Now 92|Now That's What I Call Music! 92]], which was released on 20 November 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/now-thats-what-i-call-music-92-tracklisting-revealed__11638/|title=Now That's What I Call Music 92 tracklisting revealed|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nThe song entered the UK Singles Chart at number 45.<ref name=\":0\" /> It dropped to number 68 and number 91 over the following two weeks before dropping out of the top 100.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20151127/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20151204/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref> In January 2016, the song re-entered the UK Singles Chart at number 69 following the release of the ''Keep Up'' EP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20160101/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref> The song also charted at number 78 on the [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]] Australia Top 100 Singles Chart.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video, directed by Jack Delaney, was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 15 November 2015, two days after the release of the song. As of April 2020, the music video has 40 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uBosAirL8ds|title=KSI Ft. JME - KEEP UP (Official Video)|last=|first=|date=15 November 2015|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n| title6 = \n| length10 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| title9 = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length7 = \n| title7 = \n| length6 = \n| length5 = \n| title1 = Keep Up\n| title5 = \n| length4 = \n| title4 = \n| length3 = \n| title3 = \n| length2 = \n| title2 = \n| all_writing = \n| length1 = 3:01\n| note1 = featuring [[Jme (musician)|Jme]]\n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]